title: Angles on the sphere
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$m$$ and $$n$$ be the poles of two [[great circles|Great circle]]. The interior angle $$\alpha$$ and the exterior angle $$\hat\alpha$$ of the corresponding [[digon|Spherical digon]] satisfy $$\alpha+\hat\alpha=\pi$$ and $$\cos\hat\alpha=\langle m,n\rangle,$$ so $$\cos\alpha=-\langle m,n\rangle.$$ The exterior angle is the distance between $$m$$ and $$n.$$

The area of the digon is $$2\alpha.$$